nodes.bodyText:
Yes, I overdid this a bit.
My first thought for how to simplify is to replace PROPERTY_SETTERS with a literal map listing the actual setters. That eliminates the reflection, but leaves most of the other complexity and still has helpful test output (including property names).
My second thought is to remove the property names entirely and replace the whole thing with a setup that has tests that look like this:
@Test
public void testAbfsAccessKey() {
    testPropertyGroup(HiveAzureConfig::setAbfsAccessKey, HiveAzureConfig::setAbfsStorageAccount);
}

The class is much easier to follow.
On second thought, I'll just go with the second idea. These properties aren't complicated enough that the tests really need to output exactly which properties are set.

